title: >>> The CALM Before the STORM?
body_text:
What a wild week already! The invasion looks to be in full swing for next week's DODGEBALL LX3. But before that, the calm before the storm ... or it is?
Just looking at the last entry, DODGEBALL 62 may be the last "classic" dodgeball spectacular for quite sometime. It is again no secret that a pre-meditated attack if you will is set for November 11th. However, overlooking the significance of DODGEBALL 62 would be a huge error for any elite dodgeball fan to make.
Since day one, anything and everything has happened: D-DAY 5's invasion of "The Rats", the sudden transfer from Ocean Road Park to Wall High School at DODGEBALL X6, to the more recent DODGEBALL 54 where both venues were used. As always, expect a complete night. "After-party" included!
2005 vs. 2006
November 2005; arguably the greatest month in the history of dodgeball ... fast paced-action, a plethora of new players, and overall sky-rocketing attendances.
Times have changed.
Though still breathing, will dodgeball have enough to make it to its third and perhaps final peak? Those that play week to week say yes. There is no quit in the elite group.
The question is ... can November 2006 live up to the expectations? Will it surpass last year's incredible run? The dodgeball world will find out soon enough.
